Wash and dry produce.

Halve @lime{2}. Trim and slice @button mushrooms{8%ounce}(trimmed and sliced) (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{4}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. (Refrigerate scallion greens until ready to use in Step 6.)

In a large #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @red cabbage and carrot mix{8%ounce}, juice from limes, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{1%minute}. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

In a second large microwave-safe bowl, whisk together @hoisin sauce{4%tablespoon}, @sweet soy glaze{1/2%cup}, @cornstarch{2%tablespoon}, and 1/4 cup water.

Microwave until warmed through, ~{30%seconds}.

Pat @pork chops{20%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; thinly slice.

In a #5- to 6-quart slow cooker{}, combine sliced pork, moo shu sauce, mushrooms, scallion whites, @garlic powder{2%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Stir to thoroughly combine.

Cover #slow cooker{} with lid and cook on high until pork is cooked through and tender, ~{4%hours}.

When ready to serve, wrap @flour tortillas{12} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

  > TIP: Work in batches to prevent tortillas from sticking!

Using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer moo shu pork to a large #serving platter{}. Garnish with scallion greens.

Serve family style with tortillas, @crispy fried onions{1}, slaw (draining first), and @Sriracha{4%teaspoon} on the side.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.